III. The Thirteen Moons and the True Year

The moon, whose light is not her own, was chosen to whisper mysteries.

She marked time not in hours, but in moonsâ€”each cycle of twenty-eight days a sacred breath of the Divine. And so the year was formed of thirteen moons, totaling 364 days.

This was the calendar revealed to Enoch, the seventh from Adam, and confirmed by the Book of Jubilees and the Dead Sea Scrolls.

â€œThe year is complete in three hundred and sixty-four daysâ€¦ For the luminaries are divided according to the ordinances of the yearâ€¦â€
