The Eighth Sphere â€“ Eternal Unity

And beyond the seven veils, where glory trembles into silence, there is a realm not bound by boundary, nor housed within shape. It is called the Eighth, yet it cannot be counted, for it came before time, and time has no hand upon it. The angels speak of it in hushed tones. The sages name it not, for all names fail before its presence. It is not the end, but the revelation behind all beginnings.

It is the womb of worlds and the breath before breath, the flame from which the avatars arise and to which even heaven bows. The saints call it the Supreme Reality. The Vedas name it Brahmanâ€”the unmanifested source. The Torah veils it in fire. The Qurâ€™an declares it Al-Aá¸¥ad, the One beyond comparison. The Gospels speak of it as â€œthe glory I had with the Father before the world was.â€ And in the Hermetic scrolls, it is the All, unknowable in form, but reflected in every facet of the soul.

