The soul does not stand alone. Every being it has touchedâ€”whether in harm or in helpâ€”arrives. The wounds left behind, the comfort offered, the truth denied, the love givenâ€”each becomes a presence. They do not accuse or defend. They confirm. A silent child. A forgotten enemy. A grateful stranger. Even animals, even moments of mercy shown to the earth, may appear. Creation does not forget. The soul is surrounded by memory given form.

