How to Read and Record Lunar Dates

Each month begins with the New Moon.
Count from that night:
	â€¢	New Moon night = Day 1
	â€¢	The next day = Day 2, and so on
	â€¢	When the next New Moon appears, begin again

To Record a Date:

Say the month, the day, and the solar year (AK or AC).

Example: â€œSpirali 14, 5139 AKâ€
= The 14th day after the New Moon in Spirali, in the year 5139 AK or 2025 AC.

