The soul of Taurus is slow to speak and slower to break. It rests in the earth with peace, yet its wrath is a storm that few survive. These are keepers of beauty, defenders of comfort, builders of homes and altars. They cling not from fear, but from honor â€” for that which they love, they guard with all. Their trial is in release, their virtue in loyalty. Their path is to learn that the soil must be turned for fruit to grow.

